})
```

### 3. "More than 3 players" Condition
You mentioned: *"lets have silver and bronze if there are more than 3 players"*.

*   **My Recommendation:** I suggest we **always** show Silver/Bronze colors if the rank exists (i.e., if there are 3 players, show Gold, Silver, Bronze). Restricting Silver/Bronze to only games with 4+ players might feel unfair to a group of 3 friends playing together. The 3rd person deserves their Bronze medal!
*   **Safety Check:** The code will automatically handle this. If there are only 2 players, the loop stops at index 1 (Silver), so Bronze is naturally skipped.

### 4. Animation
To make it "Seamless" but "Dramatic":
*   We will add `animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom` to the rows.
*   We will add a staggered delay so 1st place appears slightly after the others, or simply pop 1st place out visually.

### Summary of Visuals
*   **Gold:** 🏆 1st (Yellow/Gold)
*   **Silver:** 🥈 2nd (Slate/White)
*   **Bronze:** 🥉 3rd (Orange/Brown)

This provides immediate visual feedback on who won and who was close, turning the final screen into a proper award ceremony.

